derivation.yuyuan_name: early 17th cent. (in the sense 'enable sputum to be coughed up', referring to medicine): from Latin expectorat- 'expelled from the chest', from the verb expectorare, from ex- 'out' + pectus, pector- 'breast'

means.word_mean: 1. clear out the chest and lungs;
2. discharge (phlegm or sputum) from the lungs and out of the mouth
